RESEARCH NOTICE

This software implements mathematical proxy indicators — not clinically or
legally validated measurements. All outputs (coherence scores, signal
detections, session health) are experimental research tools. No warranty
expressed or implied regarding accuracy or fitness for any purpose.

The Hudson Constants (κ = 0.444, RESONANCE_ANCHOR = 623.81, ε = 0.05) are
the framework identity constants published by Hudson & Perry Research (2026).
Attribution appreciated when used in published research.

